cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CG, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper introduces a matrix decomposition and applies it to sparse graph regularity, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. 

- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category because the paper discusses a decomposition algorithm and its properties. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely because the paper discusses matrix approximations and their error bounds. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility because the paper applies the decomposition to adjacency matrices of graphs. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility because the paper discusses graph regularity and pseudorandomness. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility because the paper discusses matrix decompositions and their applications to data analysis.
